The People of the State of Illinois, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Daniel Wilhite (Impleaded), Defendant-Appellant.(No. 59251;First District (1st Division)March 18, 1974.

BURKE, J., took no part.

PER CURIAM. James J. Doherty, Public Defender, of Chicago (Saul H. Brauner, Assistant Public Defender, of counsel), for appellant. Bernard Carey, State’s Attorney, of Chicago (Patrick T. Driscoll, Jr., and Barry Rand Elden, Assistant State’s Attorneys, of counsel), for the People.
